Source: kdeutils
Section: kde
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Debian Qt/KDE Maintainers <debian-qt-kde@lists.debian.org>
Uploaders: Ana Beatriz Guerrero Lopez <ana@debian.org>, Fathi Boudra <fabo@debian.org>, Matthew Rosewarne <mrosewarne@inoutbox.com>
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 5), cmake, quilt, kdepimlibs5-dev (>= 4:3.98.0~),
 libgmp3-dev, libqimageblitz-dev, libsnmp-dev, libzip-dev, python-all-dev, libarchive-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.3


Package: kdeutils
Architecture: all
Depends: ark (>= ${binary:Version}), kcalc (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kcharselect (>= ${binary:Version}), kdessh (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kdf (>= ${binary:Version}), kfloppy (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kgpg (>= ${binary:Version}), khexedit (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kjots (>= ${binary:Version}), kmilo (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kregexpeditor (>= ${binary:Version}), ktimer (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kwalletmanager (>= ${binary:Version}), kwikdisk (>= ${binary:Version}),
 superkaramba (>= ${binary:Version}), sweeper (>= ${binary:Version})
Description: general purpose utilities from the official KDE4 release
 KDE (the K Desktop Environment) is a powerful Open Source graphical
 desktop environment for Unix workstations. It combines ease of use,
 contemporary functionality, and outstanding graphical design with the
 technological superiority of the Unix operating system.
 .
 This metapackage includes a collection of general purpose utilities
 provided with the official release of KDE4.


Package: kdeutils-dbg
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Priority: extra
Depends: kdelibs-dbg (>=4:3.98.0~)
Description: debugging symbols for kdeutils
 This package contains the debugging symbols associated with kdeutils.
 They will automatically be used by gdb for debugging kdeutils-related issues.


Package: kdeutils-dev
Section: utils
Architecture: any
Depends: ark (>= ${binary:Version}), khexedit (>= ${binary:Version}),
 kmilo (>= ${binary:Version}), kregexpeditor (>= ${binary:Version}),
 superkaramba (>= ${binary:Version})
Description: development files for the KDE4 utilities module
 This package contains development files needed to compile kdeutils
 applications.
 .
 This package is part of KDE4, as a component of the KDE4 utilities module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdeutils' packages for more information.


Package: ark
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: graphical archiving tool for KDE4
 Ark is a graphical program for managing various archive formats within the
 KDE environment. Archives can be viewed, extracted, created and modified
 from within Ark.
 .
 The program can handle various formats such as tar, gzip, bzip2, zip, rar and
 lha (if appropriate command-line programs are installed).
 .
 Ark can work closely with Konqueror in the KDE environment to handle archives,
 if you install the Konqueror Integration plugin available in the konq-plugins
 package.
 .
 This package is part of KDE4, as a component of the KDE4 utilities module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdeutils' packages for more information.


Package: kcalc
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: calculator for KDE4
 KCalc is KDE's scientific calculator.
 .
 It provides:
  * trigonometric functions, logic operations, and statistical calculations
  * easy cut and paste of numbers from/into its display
  * a results-stack which lets you conveniently recall previous results
  * configurable precision, and number of digits after the period
 .
 This package is part of KDE4, as a component of the KDE4 utilities module.
 See the 'kde' and 'kdeutils' packages for more information.


